		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2012"></a><br><code>sle2012/paper03</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2012</a> paper:</span><br><i>Termination Analysis for Higher-Order Attribute Grammars</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/LijeshKrishnan.html">Lijesh Krishnan</a>, <a href="../profile/EricVanWyk.html">Eric Van Wyk</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-36089-3_4">10.1007/978-3-642-36089-3_4</a></li>
<li>Original shorter version of <a href="../sle2012s/paper06.html"><em>Monolithic and modular termination analyses for higher-order attribute grammars</em></a> (SLE 2012 SI)</li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5d.html"><span class="tagM">T5D: Formal Methods</span></a><ul><li> The main contribution is a formal termination analysis technique for higher-order attribute grammars.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5b.html"><span class="tagL">T5B: Language Description Analysis</span></a><ul><li> It targets a meta-level correctness property (termination) of language definitions expressed as attribute grammars.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3a.html"><span class="tagL">T3A: Meta-languages</span></a><ul><li> Higher-order attribute grammars are treated as a meta-language whose specifications are analyzed.
</li></ul></li></ul>
